<p>The <b>Canary Islands stonechat</b> (<i>Saxicola dacotiae</i>), also known as the <b>Fuerteventura stonechat</b> or <b>Fuerteventura chat</b>, and formerly known as the <b>Canary Islands chat</b> due to its once widespread distribution on the <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Canary_Islands" title="Canary Islands">Canary Islands</a>. It is a sedentary resident found only on the island of <a href="http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Fuerteventura" title="Fuerteventura">Fuerteventura</a> where it is known as the <i><b>Caldereta</b></i>.</p>
<p></p>
<div id="toc" class="toc">
